00:21:06.670 --> 00:21:08.380
So I'm putting it up.

00:21:08.380 --> 00:21:09.970
So the different
stages that we have,

00:21:09.970 --> 00:21:12.250
so stage one is alpha wave.

00:21:12.250 --> 00:21:15.550
We all go into alpha wave as
soon as we close our eyes.

00:21:15.550 --> 00:21:18.790
Stage two is a slightly
deeper stage of sleep.

00:21:18.790 --> 00:21:21.820
Stage three, and in
this slide stage four,

00:21:21.820 --> 00:21:25.030
is the only time where we get
our delta sleep, which is where

00:21:25.030 --> 00:21:27.080
growth hormone comes from.

00:21:27.080 --> 00:21:32.050
So in children, 50% of our sleep
is delta, because obviously, we

00:21:32.050 --> 00:21:33.080
need to grow.

00:21:33.080 --> 00:21:38.470
But after we've reached our
ability to no longer grow,

00:21:38.470 --> 00:21:41.740
we now need growth
hormone to repair.

00:21:41.740 --> 00:21:45.130
So growth hormone is still
essential for our survival,

00:21:45.130 --> 00:21:49.180
but we're just using it to
repair instead of growing.

00:21:49.180 --> 00:21:51.130
And of course, REM,
like we discussed,

00:21:51.130 --> 00:21:54.300
those are the peaks that
you see on that graph

00:21:54.300 --> 00:21:56.470
where we get our
mental, emotional rest,

00:21:56.470 --> 00:21:59.800
our ability to retain things
that we learned that day,

00:21:59.800 --> 00:22:02.830
to process things
that we think are

00:22:02.830 --> 00:22:06.190
significant for our
survival socially.

00:22:06.190 --> 00:22:08.200
So the brain is
aware of not just

00:22:08.200 --> 00:22:11.950
our physical survival but
our emotional survival.

